  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An uncertainty quantification campaign was conducted across all five flow-speed operating points; parameter sweeps and Latin-hypercube sampling were used to characterise output sensitivity to inlet boundary conditions and fluid viscosity. Results confirmed that the RH index ranking of operating conditions is robust to ±10% variation in input parameters.",
